76561198385116343,Recommended,415200,31915268,Posted: 23 May,all,Mr G,"Easy to pick up, hard to put down... prepare to lose countless hours of your life!Just like Football Manager, Motorsport Manager allows you to take full control. Pick a race tier, choose the team or create your own from scratch, the choice is yours.There is much to consider, hiring staff, building factories, developing car components... the list is extensive, my advice? Build and improve every car component, and in this order: Brakes, Suspension, Gearbox, Engine. Aim for 75% reliability, get your race mechanics on the job!It is imperative to scout for talented designers, race mechanics and drivers. Hiring the best you can afford will improve your parts and pit stops per race ten fold.TOP TIP: Towards the middle of the season begin development of risky components. These parts will carry forward into the next season with the risk element being removed. Rinse and repeat this process!From F1 to virtual... the game features all the drama and politics of the sport. From voting on regulations to signing sponsors and dealing with the press, but the true test begins on the track. Watch a battle unfold in a 47 lap race in 3D, or 2D for less powerful computers. Come rain or shine, each race will challenge you, pause and think ahead... race strategy is crucial!This is just a brief taste of what to expect... I've logged over 50 hours to date and thankfully no issues to report, smooth as butter. Always save regularly as a precautionary.Overall no other sim compares, but patience is required. Fans of F1/GT will enjoy this experience. Build the team, master the tech, win the race!"
,Recommended,415200,31771473,Posted: 15 May,all,sCriv,"Over 200 hours played and I still can't find the words to properly describe how awesome this game is.If you're into strategy/management sims then you'll like this game.If you're into motor racing then you'll like this game.If you're into both, like I am - then you'll absolutely love this game.This game is just a pure out and out extremely detailed, multi-faceted, challenging and realistic motor racing management sim. Period.Struggling to think of any negatives, because, really, I can't, but the only slight snags are:1.) Real life teams, drivers and sponsors are not licensed, but this is not a big issue as you can quickly download MODS which provide all three very easily.2.) Long-term, the game does become repetitive and once you reach the top echelons it's very easy.Again, this isn't really a big issue, as you can always start over again, or quit your team and join a new one.If you're still bored, there are challenges to complete and obviously plenty of pretty challenging achievements to unlock.3.) The AI is pretty dumb on race day/quali at adapting to different weather conditions.I personally don't find this a big issue as if you are starting out with an uncompetitive team, you can exploit this to your advantage for some sneaky points.Besides, if you wanted to, you could always edit the game config to change the AI difficulty.Overall, this gets a 10/10.  Best game I've played all year."
