76561197995493738,Recommended,415200,31260535,Posted: 20 April,all,DeDaas,"I used to love Grand Prix Manager 2 when I was a kid and even installed it a couple of times in the last few years.. but playing a game that is by now 20 years old has its obvious drawbacks and I was happy when this finally came out. After initial release I wasn't in love straight away, but after a few months I think I feel that old feeling coming back to me!If you used to love GPM2 or GPW like I did you I think this will be worth your money, especially when you combine this with the GT DLC and the excellent ICE Mod 2017.I don't think I would use the word 'realistic' to describe this game but the game mechanics feel like they are actually portraying real world aspects of racing. For instance: having to buy HQ component X to upgrade car component Y might be a simplified mechanic, but it is actually a good way to bring across that the team that makes the right investments might have the upperhand at some point. The promotion/relegation system ofcourse is not realistic, but it adds reward to the game.One of my favorite things in the game is designing the new seasons livery. These are the small things that really add immersion to this sort of game.Something that needs work in my opinion is the staff and driver (contract) management. It seems I can not sign a driver for next season and I have to wait until a contract has expired until I can offer someone a contract without having to pay off my current driver. Also I can't change my driver order so if a driver is injured or ill I can't temporarily replace him.During the race itself I really hope the way blue flags work will get a good look at some point. If you're racing for position and about to be lapped you are basically screwed.I am currently in my second season as Mclaren (with the 2017 ICE mod) and I am enjoying it more than my first season. I love the driver switches and the teams that drop and rise in perfomance compaired to the first season. Hopefully when contract management is given more attention there will actually be a silly season which will add a lot of immersion in my opinion."
